      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Why Texas is Perfect for Solar & HVAC Upgrades</h2>
      
      <p class="mb-4">
        Texas homeowners are in a unique position to benefit from both solar panel installations and high-efficiency HVAC systems. With over 300 sunny days per year, some of the highest cooling demands in the nation, and favorable net metering policies, the Lone Star State offers exceptional ROI for home energy improvements.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>The Texas advantage:</strong> Unlike many states, Texas operates on a deregulated electricity market, meaning you can choose your provider. This gives solar owners significant leverage in negotiating buyback rates and finding the best electricity plans. Combined with the federal 30% solar tax credit and rising electricity costs (averaging 11.8¬¢/kWh statewide), typical Texas homeowners see 6-7 year payback periods on solar installations.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">üí° Did You Know?</p>
